Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.86,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:01:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.51,0:01:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.52,0:01:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.84,0:02:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't get sloppy!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you want to get killed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.51,0:02:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.18,0:02:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}There is a flower that blooms{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}within a person's heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}A flower, tinged by memories,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.89,0:02:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and bearing the scent of{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}an unforgettable someone...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.36,0:02:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Yearning"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.21,0:02:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Of the eleven smugglers,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}seven have been taken to the prison car,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.88,0:02:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the four wounded ones\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have been taken to the medical car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.22,0:02:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mission accomplished.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We're returning to Destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.89,0:02:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.23,0:03:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.83,0:03:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you guys hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}W- well... yes, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.17,0:03:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.07,0:03:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}let's have some of those famous train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}station box lunches here before we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.27,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} will depart in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But Captain Yuuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.18,0:03:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bulge, go buy enough for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.52,0:03:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't let you make any private\N{\c&He1e1e1&}calls from {\i1}Big One,{\i0} after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.59,0:03:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mm-mm, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.59,0:03:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Never mind me, are you unhurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.92,0:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Really? That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't worry, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.26,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As long as you're safe, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.27,0:03:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Happy birthday, Catalina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.61,0:03:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.61,0:03:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll give you your present\N{\c&He1e1e1&}some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.94,0:04:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you, Bulge. Just hearing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your voice is present enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}See you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm glad that you like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.56,0:04:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a little drab in here,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so I tried to dress it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, yeah... Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a request to take some leave\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the base. Can I get you to sign it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.58,0:04:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.58,0:04:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's unusual, huh?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The captain spacing off like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.25,0:04:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That must have reminded him\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of a woman from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.26,0:04:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean, a Modesty woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Want to bet on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.26,0:04:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sure. 10,000 says\N{\c&He1e1e1&}it's a woman from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.26,0:04:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:04:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, I thought you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just barely took some leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.60,0:05:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Louis-san{\i0} has taken leave a total of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}three times. However, in a woman's case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.54,0:05:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say no more. So, what kind of trouble\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are you going to make on your leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.88,0:05:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not going to make any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm just doing some shopping,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reading, and cleaning my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.22,0:05:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd also like to watch my dramas and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the sports broadcasts that I've recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.89,0:05:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd also like to go learn to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That would take a year to do,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}if it were me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But why don't any of you take any leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.23,0:05:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even if I did,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}there's nothing that I would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.57,0:05:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Besides, once you get to our ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}it just doesn't feel right\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to take any leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.90,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Especially when you have a captain
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}who has only taken a single day's leave\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ever since he joined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a right allowed for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by the rules that you deserve to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.58,0:05:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Interstellar Express No. 134\N{\c&He1e1e1&}appears to be stalled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.89,0:05:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}in the Melbiunous Zone of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the 6th Ulysses Star System.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon, please hurry\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to their assistance at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.54,0:06:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.54,0:06:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you, always.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, about what we discussed,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we'll be counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.55,0:06:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right. I'll think up a menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.22,0:06:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What you already have will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.55,0:06:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But it's such a special occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's pretty fast\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for a commuter train.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, and I don't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}recognize the whistle, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.57,0:06:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've finished delivering 45 passengers\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to the Corneila Royal Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.91,0:06:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Bruce. I've finished my\N{\c&He1e1e1&}third run to the Hotel Garden Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}90 passengers delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.25,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy. Once the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}replacement train arrives,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you are to take care of seeing off\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the passengers you just delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.86,0:07:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't sound so tortured, guys.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This is part of the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.55,0:07:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It couldn't have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.22,0:07:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It must be that flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.22,0:07:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is something the matter, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, sorry, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.57,0:07:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It doesn't look like anyone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's a shop that's open\N{\c&He1e1e1&}across the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.24,0:07:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Because this shop is so charming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.14,0:07:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay. It says\N{\c&He1e1e1&}"Be back soon" right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.91,0:07:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And how soon is soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:07:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look, I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.19,0:08:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}H- hi there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry about that.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll open up right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You see? Soon, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.87,0:08:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For crying out loud,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the captain sure is tough on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.21,0:08:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're so right. That's why he\N{\c&He1e1e1&}can't hold onto any girlfriends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.21,0:08:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the kind of place\N{\c&He1e1e1&}where you'd want a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.23,0:08:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh? Captan Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bulge, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter? Captain, I had\N{\c&He1e1e1&}no idea you were that kind of person!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And here, in such a conspicuous place!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, I've misjudged you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.85,0:09:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Procyon rail distortion accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean the worst mishap\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in Galaxy Railways' history?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.86,0:09:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This girl is the lone\N{\c&He1e1e1&}survivor of that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.80,0:09:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Every once in a while,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}she comes to see me like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Today, I came to tell him\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that I graduated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.54,0:09:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that right? I'm sorry for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my indecorous misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.21,0:09:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I saw the news reports\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That must have been\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when you were still...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.55,0:09:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was ten at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And that little girl grew up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be such a pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.89,0:09:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So even you are capable of complimenting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a girl to her face, eh Bulge?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:09:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}W- well, I... I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:09:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, no, coming from you,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}it was well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.90,0:10:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come on, please don't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make fun of me, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.24,0:10:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As you can see, he may\N{\c&He1e1e1&}be a social basket case,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but as a platoon member,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he's very capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's conscientious in his work,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}so ignoring orders and charging\N{\c&He1e1e1&}headlong into a situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or openly challenging someone of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a senior rank, like his captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.25,0:10:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...is something he would never do, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}C- Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.93,0:10:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whoops, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.10,0:10:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I just remembered, I have an important\N{\c&He1e1e1&}matter to take care of at Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.27,0:10:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Forgive me, but I have to head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.60,0:10:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Congratulations on graduating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}C- Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Bulge-san,{\i0} why did you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}decide to join the SDF?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ever since I was a child, I had\N{\c&He1e1e1&}been somewhat awestruck by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.58,0:11:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but it's probably because of something\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that happened this one time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.08,0:11:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that I seriously set my heart on joining.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.25,0:11:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What one time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.91,0:11:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The accident you were involved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here there was this terrible scene, where\N{\c&He1e1e1&}no one was expected to have survived,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.25,0:11:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and an SDF platoon member\N{\c&He1e1e1&}rescued this little girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.22,0:11:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}even while suffering\N{\c&He1e1e1&}injuries to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.26,0:11:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The image of it all just shook me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.93,0:11:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Actually, it was only recently that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I found out that it was Captain Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I lost my parents and brother that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.94,0:11:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But that accident did serve\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to steer me toward my life's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.62,0:11:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your life's work?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.62,0:11:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it some kind of profession\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in the medical field?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.12,0:11:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Does that mean you've\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just graduated from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.62,0:12:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.56,0:12:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was unable to recover\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the shock of the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and had become anorexic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.23,0:12:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And then {\i1}Yuuki-san...{\i0} I mean,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain {\i1}Yuuki-san{\i0} said this to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.90,0:12:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right now, what do you think your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama and Papa up in Heaven want most?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.24,0:12:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's for you to eat the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}food that's in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}At first, no matter what I ate,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}it was as if I was chewing on sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.25,0:12:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But little by little, I began\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to consider it as tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.26,0:12:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And then, I started to think,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my father, mother, brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.26,0:12:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and all the other people\N{\c&He1e1e1&}who died in that accident
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}probably would have liked to go on living,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to eat many other delicious things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.27,0:12:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So I became a chef. Strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.61,0:12:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, it isn't strange at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.61,0:13:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And today, you came to tell\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that to the captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Would you like me to tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.23,0:13:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- if it's okay with you...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could I ask you... to see me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so happy!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, can I have one of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.92,0:13:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, hey! That's bad manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.92,0:13:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, {\i1}Yuuki-kun,{\i0} how come\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you're always so uptight?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- I'm not uptight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.93,0:13:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This isn't the first time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you've ever had dinner with a girl
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.87,0:13:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}in a place like this, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.27,0:13:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.27,0:13:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you, by any chance,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki {\i1}Wataru-san's?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.94,0:13:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes, I am his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.55,0:14:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you know my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.22,0:14:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're gallantly following in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your father's footsteps, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, no, I'm still not even a captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.23,0:14:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, boy! Listen to you, Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um, who is the captain now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you for your service.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This is my treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.91,0:14:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.58,0:14:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Schwanheld Bulge...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so glad you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.59,0:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But there's no guarantee\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'll be safe next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.93,0:14:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Besides, not all of my duties\N{\c&He1e1e1&}come with danger attached to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.27,0:14:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Forgive me. I know that, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.94,0:15:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Catalina...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, there's this shop that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I've wanted to take you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then let's go right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.89,0:15:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't pick up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.89,0:15:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, we might be scrambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And here we are, finally together...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.23,0:15:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks for the drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, Honey, {\i1}Catalina-chan{\i0} says she needs\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to discuss the menu she's catering for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She's a meticulous girl, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's something I want to give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.58,0:15:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm on Tabito now. I'm on my way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.92,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The train on Track 1 bound for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Kleznard is about to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Passengers boarding are asked to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}please wait behind the white line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.93,0:15:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Catalina...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.88,0:16:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is your family doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.88,0:16:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. I'm shocked at how much\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the children are growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But you only had half a day. You have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to feel sorry doing this to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, they'll understand someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.23,0:16:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about you? If this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hadn't come up, you'd be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.23,0:16:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It can't be helped.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}But I think she'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a luckless job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.24,0:16:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Looks like I win the bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I won the bet. I'm the one who\N{\c&He1e1e1&}said it was a woman from his past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.91,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nope, I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.58,0:16:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Because she's not a woman\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from his past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Heh, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dad won't ever be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I've got a one-day pass. No matter what{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}may happen in this universe,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.18,0:18:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I will make sure I see you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I know that you are{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}coming to say goodbye.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I, too, understand{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you never know{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when you might meet with the{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}same fate that Captain Yuuki did.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.56,0:18:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I know that you do not want me{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to go through the same sorrow{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that I did in my youth{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when I lost my family,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.90,0:18:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and that this is surely your{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}way of showing kindness to me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.51,0:19:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I proposed to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}With me, she will be able\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to realize her modest dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.95,0:19:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can always be at her side,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to nestle with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Her dream...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.20,0:19:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}May you have every happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.55,0:19:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She sure was pretty, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.58,0:20:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A Modesty woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.92,0:20:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Give it up, {\i1}Yuuki-kun.{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}She's waiting for someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.59,0:20:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Someone who?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know, but there's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}someone out there in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.39,0:20:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that she used to love a lot,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.26,0:20:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How would you know that, Louis?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.93,0:20:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, when we get back, I'm on leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.27,0:20:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, please see to it that you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take some leave sometime, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.27,0:20:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I understand it makes it more difficult\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for David and Bruce to take any.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.28,0:20:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Hey...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- That goes for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.61,0:20:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't worry about taking time off.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a right that you deserve.
